<font color="#FF0000" size="3">

<H2>OCD and Parenting</H2>
<H4>by Hugh F. Johnson, M.D., and Jay Fruehling, M.L.S.</H4>

</font>
<hr>

	The Obsessive Compulsive Foundation has published this brief 
(28 pages) but very useful guide, OCD and Parenting, for parents of 
children with OCD (obsessive compulsive disorder).  Written by 
treatment professionals, the text is user-friendly, in part because 
of its conversational question-and-answer format.  The book 
includes a bibliography and lists additional resources.  It is 
available from the OCD Foundation, P.O. Box 70, Milford, CT 06460-
0700.  The price is $4 for non-foundation members.
 
<hr><h6>
<p align=center><a href="/poc.htm">CONTACT</a> | <a href="/joinform.htm">MEMBERSHIP</a> | <a href="mailto:barbara@nami.org">WEBMASTER</a></p></h6>
