<!-- NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI -->
<!-- NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI -->
<!-- NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI NAMI -->

<hr>


<H2>Bipolar Risk</H2>
<HR>	


	According to an article in the fall 1995 NARSAD Research 
Newsletter ("Advances in Genetics of Psychiatric Disorders" by Anne 
Brown), "For bipolar disorder, if an individual has one affected 
parent, the risk of developing the disorder is 27%, and if both 
parents are affected, the risk increases to 74%.  For 
schizophrenia, the corresponding risks are 9% and 46%."

