<p>
	Measurements were taken while the patients were taking the drug, five days after discontinuing the drug, and 30 to 35 days after 
haloperidol discontinuation.  There were no significant differences found after five days off the drug, suggesting that effects of 
discontinuation are not rapid, but differences were seen at 30 to 35 days.  
<p>
	This study helps explain the effectiveness of neuroleptics, since haloperidol decreased glucose utilization in areas in which 
functional alterations can lead to psychosis.

