<STRONG>Copy Regulations</STRONG><br><br>


<P>Minimum size ad acceptable is one inch (i.e., 12 lines of type) set in six-point 
type. There are 38 characters to a line, including word spaces. When an 
advertisement is set in capital letters, there are 34 characters to a line, 
including word spaces. If an advertisement employs display type, white space 
or exceeds one inch, it is then charged on the basis of incremental quarter 
inches. Minimum depth -- 1 column, 1 inch; 2 columns, 2 inches; 3 columns, 4 
inches; 4 columns, 6 inches.</P>



<STRONG>Box Numbers</STRONG><br><br>


<P>Box numbers require a full line. Replies will be mailed daily, and the box number 
will remain in effect for six months. </P>



